# deploy

A deploy without a checklist is roulette. Do not skip phases.

---

## Phase 1 ‚Äî Pre-deploy checklist

**STOP on any single "no":**

- [ ] **Tests green** in CI/CD or locally on the destination branch.
- [ ] **MRs/PRs merged** ‚Äî no open MR blocking the release.
- [ ] **Migrations** ‚Äî if any, already applied in staging before prod. Use `/migrate`.
- [ ] **Version/tag** ‚Äî prod requires a tag (`v1.2.3`) or an explicit release marker.
- [ ] **Changelog updated** ‚Äî the user knows what is being deployed.
- [ ] **Rollback plan** ‚Äî how to revert if prod breaks. Is the previous deploy known?

If any item is "no" ‚Üí **STOP**, tell the user, do not continue.

---

## Phase 2 ‚Äî Staging (unless going dev‚Üíprod directly)

Sequence: `dev` ‚Üí `test/staging` ‚Üí `prod`.

Verify in staging:
- [ ] The app starts without errors (health check endpoint, startup logs).
- [ ] Smoke tests / manual check of the critical user flows.
- [ ] Migrations applied correctly.
- [ ] External integrations (API, queues, S3) work.

**Do not deploy to prod** until staging passes.

---

## Phase 3 ‚Äî Deploy to the target environment

**Only after an explicit OK from the user.**

Show the command before running it:
```
–î–µ–ø–ª–æ—é –≤ <–æ–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ>: <–∫–æ–º–∞–Ω–¥–∞>
```

Typical commands:
```bash
# Docker Compose
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml pull && docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

# Kubernetes
kubectl set image deployment/<name> <container>=<image>:<tag> -n <namespace>
kubectl rollout status deployment/<name> -n <namespace>

# Git-based (Heroku, Render, Railway)
git push <remote> <branch>

# SSH + pull
ssh user@host "cd /app && git pull && systemctl restart app"
```

Deploy logs stay on screen. On error ‚Üí **STOP**, go to rollback.

---

## Phase 4 ‚Äî Post-deploy verify

- [ ] **Health check** ‚Äî HTTP 200 on `/health`, `/ping`, or the home page.
- [ ] **Logs** ‚Äî no ERROR/CRITICAL in the first 2‚Äì3 minutes after the deploy.
- [ ] **Key metrics** ‚Äî latency, error rate, queue depth show no abnormal rise.
- [ ] **Smoke test** ‚Äî one critical user flow, by hand.
- [ ] **Version** ‚Äî the `/version` endpoint or header returns the expected version.

**Exit:** all green ‚Üí the deploy succeeded.

---

## Emergency rollback

If verify fails, tell the user:

```
–°–¢–û–ü. ROLLBACK.
–û–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ: <prod/staging>
–ü—Ä–∏—á–∏–Ω–∞: <—á—Ç–æ —Å–ª–æ–º–∞–ª–æ—Å—å>.
```

Typical rollback:
```bash
# Docker: previous tag
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml pull <image>:<prev-tag>
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

# Kubernetes
kubectl rollout undo deployment/<name> -n <namespace>

# Git revert + push
git revert HEAD && git push
```

After a rollback ‚Äî record the incident; do not redeploy without a root cause.
